 Strategic LeadershipDefine and execute the vision and multi-year strategy for Data Science and Machine Learning across all Careem verticals.Closely partner with product, engineering, and business leaders to identify and prioritize high-impact AI opportunities with measurable business ROI.Drive standardization, scalability, and platformization across ML systems to accelerate delivery and innovation.Evangelize AI across the company, ensuring alignment between AI investments and Careem’s overall strategic priorities.Build, lead, and inspire a high-performing team of 30+ ML engineers and data scientists distributed across geographies and domains.Foster a culture of inclusion, experimentation, and excellence — empowering teams to take ownership and innovate.Ensure clear ownership and accountability across core DS streams, and continuously evolve team structure for scale and accelerating impact.Mentor emerging leaders and invest in developing technical and leadership capabilities across the organization.Oversee the design, development, and deployment of end-to-end ML systems — from data collection and feature engineering to productionized models and monitoring.Partner with engineering to ensure robust infrastructure for training, retraining, and serving ML models at scale.Define and oversee the technical AI roadmap and direction for the team.Lead innovation in Generative AI and LLM applications, ensuring Careem stays at the forefront of applied AI technologies.Champion MLOps and automation to reduce experimentation-to-production cycle time.Ensure each Data Science domain delivers measurable impact aligned with company OKRs and product outcomes.Collaborate with vertical leaders to embed ML into user-facing experiences (e.g., personalized discovery, dynamic ranking, ETA prediction, integrity systems).Establish clear success metrics and measurement frameworks for AI-driven initiatives with clear AI impact accounting.Champion a data-driven culture across Careem — ensuring in